laboratory_examinations.findings: There is mild bilateral lower lobe dependent atelectasis. The hepatic parenchyma enhances homogeneously. No focal liver lesions are identified. There is no intra or extrahepatic biliary duct dilatation. The portal vein is patent. The gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, adrenal glands, and kidneys are unremarkable. The stomach and small bowel are unremarkable. The retrocecal appendix is dilated to 16 mm and demonstrates surrounding fat stranding, compatible with appendicitis. There is mild wall thickening within the cecum along the base of the appendix. The remainder of the colon is within normal limits. There is no free fluid or free air in the abdomen. Small pericecal lymph nodes do not meet CT size criteria. There is no pathologically enlarged abdominal lymph nodes. The abdominal aorta is normal in caliber. Scattered aortic and bilateral iliac artery calcifications are seen. There is also noncalcified atheromatous disease within the inferior aspect of the aorta as well as within the left common iliac artery. The bladder is unremarkable. There is no free fluid in the pelvis. No pathologically enlarged pelvic lymph nodes are seen. No osseous lesions concerning for infection or malignancy. Multilevel degenerative changes are seen throughout the imaged spine.
